    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="63"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/938.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Republican Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Manchu Government having entered into negotiation with Republic of China for
                    purpose of abdicating their entire sovereign rights, power and privileges, we
                    fervently pray recognition, to avoid disastrous interregnum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wang Chung Hui</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
